snippet.textDisplay: This is phenomenal. I'm amazed on the in depth understanding of Xulfi about the languages and its blending. As a matter of fact Push is the only language in Pakistan which has the intrinsic ability to be easily blended with English. Surprisingly you will find most of the naturally English speaking people in Pakistan from Pathan community. Pushto and English have very close similarities like accent, prosodic, elision. A big ovation to sir Xulfi on finding and blending such features of two languages.
